{
  "id": "daily-authoring-workflow",
  "lang": "en",
  "slug": "daily-authoring-workflow",
  "title": "The Daily Authoring Workflow",
  "description": "A practical rhythm for using Codex in ongoing documentation work.",
  "tags": [
    "workflow",
    "authoring"
  ],
  "status": "published",
  "updatedAt": "2026-03-19T00:00:00.000Z",
  "content": {
    "version": 1,
    "blocks": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "id": "block-1",
        "level": 1,
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The Daily Authoring Workflow"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "id": "block-2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Once your docs site already exists, use Codex in this rhythm:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "list",
        "id": "block-3",
        "style": "numbered",
        "items": [
          {
            "id": "element-3-item-1",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "read first, do not write immediately"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "id": "element-4-item-1",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "identify the target page before deciding whether to create or update"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "id": "element-5-item-1",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "make small, explicit, reviewable page changes"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "id": "element-6-item-1",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "treat status transitions as a separate action through `page_set_status`"
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "id": "block-7",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A good developer prompt usually includes:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "list",
        "id": "block-8",
        "style": "bulleted",
        "items": [
          {
            "id": "element-8-item-1",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "the exact `projectRoot`"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "id": "element-9-item-1",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "the target language such as `zh` or `en`"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "id": "element-10-item-1",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "which page to work on: `pageId` or `slug`"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "id": "element-11-item-1",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "the intended outcome: create content, revise content, or change status"
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "id": "block-12",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "That makes it much easier for Codex to stay on the correct MCP workflow."
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}
